ChemBytes Draw is a compact .NET component allowing developers to integrate advanced chemical drawing and chemical information processing into any  .NET project (WPF or Windows Forms).

This is a 30 day evaluation version, which later can be unlocked. No registration required.

As part of a .NET application, ChemBytes Draw on demand displays a fully featured chemical drawing editor, which also supports organometallic, polymer and peptide drawing. Content can be imported from other third party chemical drawing tools, e.g. ISIS/Symyx/Accelrys Draw, ChemDraw, Marvin, etc., via MDL clipboard content or via MDL format export files, including V3000 format. When the user closes the editor, the API takes over and exposes the chemical information for use by your own application. Thus, the molecular weights and elemental formulas of all entered reactants and products, their InChIKeys, bitmap and vector images, bounding boxes, the MDL reaction and molfiles, and the internal XML file format for database storage, etc. are available for further processing. ChemBytes Draw is written in 100% managed code, i.e. it is no wrapper around an existing Java or C++ functionality.

A sample Visual Studio project and sample files are available from the project site.
summary: ChemBytes Draw is a .NET component allowing developers to integrate advanced chemical drawing and chemical information processing into any .NET project (WPF or Windows Forms).

Features:
* The dump output is separated from the targeted dump media by the familiar TextWriter interface.
* The programmer can dump the value of any type of object: primitive and  enum types (including those marked with FlagsAttribute), custom classes, struct-s, collections, etc.
* For complex type objects (classes and structs) the dumper outputs the names and the values of the properties.
* The dump is recursive: the complex members of the dumped object are dumped indented.
* Dumps the elements of sequences (arrays, lists, dictionaries, etc.)
* Handles circular references.
* The developers can easily customize various aspects of the dump by using an attribute (DumpAttribute) on the classes and their members, such as:
    - the order in which the properties are dumped;
    - formatting of the property names and/or values;
    - suppressing the dump of some uninteresting properties;
    - masking the values of sensitive (e.g. PII) properties;
    - the depth of the recursion into complex members;
    - the maximum number of dumped elements of sequence properties.
* The dumper picks the customization attributes also from buddy classes declared with MetadataTypeAttribute.
* Even if the class doesn't have any attributes, the programmer can still pass a metadata class as a separate parameter to the dumping method. This allows for control over the dump of BCL and third party classes.
* Build and tested with .NET 4.0, 4.5, 4.5.1. This package targets .NET 4.0.
summary: Easy to integrate and easy to use component that dumps the value of a .NET object in a text form. Helpful for debugging and logging purposes.

ChemBytes Draw is a compact .NET component allowing developers to integrate advanced chemical drawing and chemical information processing into any  .NET project (WPF or Windows Forms).

This is a 30 day evaluation version, which later can be unlocked. No registration required.

As part of a .NET application, ChemBytes Draw on demand displays a fully featured chemical drawing editor, which also supports organometallic, polymer and peptide drawing. Content can be imported from other third party chemical drawing tools, e.g. ISIS/Symyx/Accelrys Draw, ChemDraw, Marvin, etc., via MDL clipboard content or via MDL format export files, including V3000 format. When the user closes the editor, the API takes over and exposes the chemical information for use by your own application. Thus, the molecular weights and elemental formulas of all entered reactants and products, their InChIKeys, bitmap and vector images, bounding boxes, the MDL reaction and molfiles, and the internal XML file format for database storage, etc. are available for further processing. reCAPTCHA for .NET allows a developer to easily integrate Google's reCAPTCHA service (the most popular captcha control used by millions of sites) in an ASP.NET Web Forms or ASP.NET MVC web application.

The primary features of the library are:
* Renders recaptcha control with appropriate options.
* Verifies user's answer to reCAPTCHA's challenge.
* Supports ASP.NET 4.0, 4.5, and 4.5.1.
* Supports ASP.NET MVC 4 and 5. 
* The library currently supports Google's reCAPTCHA API v1. Support for API v2 is coming soon and the support for v1 will remain in tact as long as Google does the same.

reCAPTCHA for .NET has the best and most up-to-date documentation among all the other competing libraries.
summary: Quickly add reCAPTCHA (the most popular captcha service used by millions of sites) in an ASP.NET Web Forms or ASP.NET MVC web application.
